<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8886535-erin-bottger-bouma"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1334834146i/8886535._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8886535-erin-bottger-bouma">Erin Bottger (Bouma)</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Our Book Club discussed this book today. <br />1. Was there any way the Great Galveston Hurricane could have been anticipated, given the state of meteorolog<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Our Book Club discussed this book today. <br />1. Was there any way the Great Galveston Hurricane could have been anticipated, given the state of meteorology at the time? <br />2. How important was the conflict between Isaac and Joseph? Do you think their rivalry began in childhood or was related to their professional lives? <br />3. Did you like or respect Isaac? What about the rest of his life?<br />4. Do you think Erik Larson was able to successfully construct a convincing narrative flow about this historical event? Do some of the snippets and technical details feel like padding or do they contribute to understanding the story?<br />5. How did you feel as you "lived through" the disaster with the characters? What shocked you? Appalled you? Broke your heart? <br />6. How effective was Larson in capturing the sensory atmosphere of Galveston: smells, sights, sounds, feel?<br />7. The political struggles between the Cuban forecasters and the U.S. Weather Bureau played a role in this tragedy. Do you think there could have been a different outcome had it been different?<br />8. Did this book give you a window on everyday life in America and Galveston at the turn of the century?<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
